<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><h4><a href="https://chessolympiad.fide.com"><strong>Official Website</strong></a></h4> <p>Follow the games here: <a href="https://www.chess.com/events/2022-fide-chess-olympiad">Chess.com</a> | <a href="https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/olympiad-chennai-2022-open">Chess24</a> | <a href="https://lichess.org/broadcast/44th-chess-olympiad-2022--open/round-1/T1CUcvwV">Lichess</a> | <a href="https://nxt.chessbomb.com/events/2022-fide-chess-olympiad">Chessbomb</a> | <a href="https://chess-results.com/tnr653631.aspx">Chess-Results</a></p> <hr/> <p><strong>CHENNAI</strong> - The countdown has begun for the world’s biggest chess event, the <a href="https://i.imgur.com/zJI6QF4.png">44th International Chess Olympiad</a>, scheduled to take place from July 28 to August 10 at Poonjeri Village in Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu. The grand inaugural ceremony featuring the rich culture and tradition of Tamil Nadu will be attended by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, Chief Minister M.K. Stalin, and other special invitees at Nehru Indoor Stadium on July 28.</p> <p>The Olympiad was originally scheduled to take place in Russia but due to the ongoing Russian-Ukraine war, the International Chess Federation (FIDE) started looking for new bidders. India emerged the topper among other countries and won the opportunity to host the high-profile event for the first time. The Union Government provided the hosting rights of the world’s biggest chess event to Tamil Nadu.</p> <hr/> <h4><strong>Standings</strong> (after Round 6)</h4> <table><thead> <tr> <th align="center"><strong>#</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>FED</strong></th> <th align="left"><strong>Captain</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>Rtg.</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>MP</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>SB</strong></th> <th align="center"><strong>Pts.</strong></th> </tr> </thead><tbody> <tr> <td align="center">1</td> <td align="left">🇦🇲 Armenia</td> <td align="left">Arman